agreed_on_going_public_at":"2020-08-11T10:37:09.482Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"hi team,\n I found  Unrestricted File Upload Vulnerabilities on  https://app.dropcontact.io/app/upload/.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n\n  1. Create an account in https://app.dropcontact.io/app/\n  1. go to https://app.dropcontact.io/app/upload/\n  1. try to upload html file , you will see message only (: .csv, .txt, .xls, .xlsx) allowed.\n  1. change the HTML file extension to txt and try to upload it again \n  1. it work and the file successfully uploaded\n\n## Supporting Material/References:\nhttps://www.exploit-db.com/docs/english/45074-file-upload-restrictions-bypass.pdf\nhttps://www.opswat.com/blog/file-upload-protection-best-practices\n\n{F932903} \n\n\n## how to fix \nTo avoid these types of file upload attacks: \n1. File type verification\n1. Restrict specific file extensions \n1. add verification in both back-End and front-End\n\n## Impact\n\nthis is not really impact because the app not report the full path for the files uploaded.\nbut if an attacker found a way to get the path . it wil be used to get attackes like xss or even rce .\n\nBest Regards,\n@omarelfarsaoui","weakness":{"id":148,"name":"Unrestricted Upload of File with Dangerous Type"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":932903,"file_name":"poc-2020-08-01_17.39.00.mp4","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/FkSRjbiXduYRP9HfLmhNimkZ?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22poc-2020-08-01_17.39.00.mp4%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27poc-2020-08-01_17.39.00.mp4\u0026response-content-type=video%2Fmp4\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQXG6W2HKE%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T085114Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECgaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJHMEUC